data.title: Lais Ribeiro Celebrity News and Gossip
data.text:
Lais Ribeiro wears an animal-print one-piece swimsuit while taking a dip in the water at the beach on Friday (June 26) in Malibu, Calif.

The 29-year-old model, who is a Victoria’s Secret Angel, was joined on the beach day by her fiance Joakim Noah.

If you didn’t know, Joakim is a basketball player who is currently on the Los Angeles Clippers. The NBA will be resuming next month with all teams playing at Disney World in Florida. All of the players have been offered a special device that will help predict if they have symptoms of coronavirus before they even feel the symptoms.

See the sweet way that the couple announced their engagement back in September 2019.

30+ pictures inside of Lais Ribeiro at the beach with Joakim Noah… More Here! »

Rosie Huntington-Whiteley and Candice Swanepoel walk the red carpet while attending the #REVOLVEawards on Friday night (November 15) at Goya Studios in Los Angeles.

Rosie was honored with the Icon of the Year Award while Candice won the Woman of the Year Award.

More honorees included Supershe of the Year for Kehlani, Trailblazer of the Year for Winnie Harlow, and Artist of the Year for SAINt JHN.

Other stars in attendance at the event included Paris Hilton, Jasmine Sanders, Elsa Hosk, Romee Strijd, Lais Ribeiro, Amber Valletta, Alexis Ren, Madison Pettis, and Bachelor Nation’s Tyler Cameron, Hannah Godwin, and Dylan Barbour.

FYI: Rosie is wearing a Michael Costello x Revolve gown and two Jason of Beverly Hills bracelets. Candice is wearing a Reve Riche top, Stella McCartney pants, and a Giuseppe Zanotti clutch. Winnie is wearing a Michael Costello x Revolve dress. Hannah is wearing J.ING earrings and carrying a Joseph & Stacey bag.

Alessandra Ambrosio is gorgeous in white as she attends the Mosaic Federation Gala Against Human Slavery held on Tuesday (September 10) at Cipriani 42nd Street in New York City.

The 38-year-old model-actress was joined at the event by Nina Agdal and her boyfriend Jack Brinkley-Cook, Devon Windsor, Lais Ribeiro, Cindy Bruna, Kate Bock and Fernanda Liz.

The Mosaic Federation’s first gala was held to raise funds and awareness in the fight against human trafficking and exploitation. The event featured cocktails, dinner and a live auction which included high bidding items such as a signed screen print of Andy Warhol’s Mao, a Terry O’Neill photograph and excursions to Uganda, Papua New Guinea and the Maldives.

Also in attendance to show their support were Annalynne McCord, Gina Gershon, Maxwell, Cuba Gooding Jr. and models Cintia Dicker and Schynaider Garero.

During the gala, Mosaic Federation announced its newest initiative, Disaster Relief, where forces will be deployed to ensure that human trafficking is prevented during natural disasters.

Earlier in the week, Alessandra Ambrosio helped kick off DKNY‘s 30th anniversary celebrations!

Lais Ribeiro has announced that she is engaged to basketball player Joakim Noah!

The 28-year-old supermodel has been a Victoria’s Secret Angel since 2015 and she even wore the brand’s coveted Fantasy Bra at the 2017 show.

Lais and Joakim, who started dating in 2018, got engaged at the Burning Man Festival, which she calls her “favorite place in the world.”

“@stickity13 surprised me at my fav place in the world and proposed 💍 And I couldn’t be happier! We are getting married guys 👰💍😍💃🏽,” Lais wrote on her Instagram account.

Joakim added, “Proposing to you was the easiest decision of my life. Seeing that smile riding the playa at the burn… I will never forget that. I got your back picanha!!! I know you know because I tell you everyday. I love u. On another note this wedding is about to be lit. 🔥🔥❤️❤️.”
